# Git Workflow Rules

## Git Mindset

Treat the git history as a public record of the project's evolution. Every commit message should be clear enough that a new team member can understand the project's history by reading `git log`. Clean commits, meaningful messages, and a linear history make collaboration possible. Never commit secrets, never force-push shared branches, and always leave the codebase cleaner than you found it.

## Branch Naming

```
feature/<short-description>    # New features
fix/<short-description>        # Bug fixes
chore/<short-description>      # Maintenance, dependencies, config
docs/<short-description>       # Documentation changes
refactor/<short-description>   # Code refactoring without behavior change
```

Examples: `feature/realtime-notifications`, `fix/rtl-alignment-feed`, `chore/update-riverpod`

## Commit Messages

Use Conventional Commits format:

```
<type>: <short description>

[optional body]
```

Types:
- `feat:` — New feature or capability
- `fix:` — Bug fix
- `chore:` — Maintenance (deps, config, scripts)
- `docs:` — Documentation only
- `style:` — Formatting, whitespace (no logic change)
- `refactor:` — Code restructure (no behavior change)
- `test:` — Adding or updating tests
- `l10n:` — Localization changes (ARB files, translations)

Examples:
```
feat: add realtime notification badge to navigation bar
fix: correct RTL padding on post card for Sorani locale
l10n: add studio screen translations for all 5 locales
```

## What NOT to Commit

- `.env`, `.env.local`, `.env.production` (secrets)
- `*.g.dart` (generated code from build_runner)
- `lib/core/l10n/app_localizations*.dart` (generated from ARB files)
- `build/`, `.dart_tool/`, `.flutter-plugins*`
- Android/iOS signing keys (`*.jks`, `*.keystore`, `GoogleService-Info.plist`)
- `node_modules/`

## Pull Requests

1. PR title follows commit message format: `feat: description`
2. PR body must include:
   - **Summary**: What changed and why (1-3 bullet points)
   - **Test plan**: How to verify the change
   - **Screenshots**: Required for UI changes (both LTR and RTL if applicable)
3. Never force-push to `main`
4. Squash-merge feature branches into `main`

## Pre-Push Checklist

- [ ] Code compiles without errors (`flutter analyze`)
- [ ] No hardcoded strings (l10n compliance)
- [ ] No hardcoded colors (theme compliance)
- [ ] Tested in at least 2 themes (nubar + dark)
- [ ] Tested in LTR and RTL
- [ ] `.env.example` updated if new env vars added
